@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Balaby' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  To move the ball, you have to rotate the game board by clicking
on one of the 'rotation arrows' located at either side of the game
board. the arrow located at the right rotates the board clockwise
and the arrow located at the left rotates the board
counterclockwise. If there is no horizontal bar under the ball, the
ball will fall, until it reaches a horizontal bar or the edge of
the game board.

  As only a portion of the entire game board is shown at a time,
when a ball falls towards the lower part of the visible area of the
board and there are no horizontal bar to stop it, the ball will go
'through' to the lower side of the board and the game will then
display the lower part of the board where the ball goes to. The
ball will continue to fall, until it reaches either the edge or a
horizontal bar.

  Watch out for 'traps' or bars that are placed in such a way so
that you have to go back to where the ball previously was... adding
some extra moves in the process.

  If the ball is stuck or you want to restart a game, click on the
'Replay' button (or with the Right-Amiga and 'R' key combination),
which will restart the game with the current game board.

  You can change the ball's colour by clicking on it, this will
cycle through the available colours (up to 16 colours) from the
Workbench palette.

  Have fun!

@endnode

